        <rating/>
        <publication-year>1859</publication-year>
        <review>&lt;span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 20px; font-family: sans-serif; "/&gt;&lt;p style="margin-top: 0.4em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;b&gt;A Tale of Two Cities&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#160;(&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1859_in_literature" title="1859 in literature" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;1859&lt;/a&gt;) is a&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Novel" title="Novel" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;novel&lt;/a&gt;&#160;by&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charles_Dickens" title="Charles Dickens" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Charles Dickens&lt;/a&gt;, set in&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/London" title="London" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;London&lt;/a&gt;&#160;and&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paris" title="Paris" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Paris&lt;/a&gt;&#160;before and during the&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/French_Revolution" title="French Revolution" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;French Revolution&lt;/a&gt;. With well&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_best-selling_books" title="List of best-selling books" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;over 200 million copies sold&lt;/a&gt;, it ranks among the most famous works in the history of fictional literature.&lt;sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-1" style="line-height: 1em; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; "&gt;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A_Tale_of_Two_Cities#cite_note-1" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; white-space: nowrap; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;&lt;span&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;2&lt;span&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="margin-top: 0.4em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;The novel depicts the plight of the French peasantry demoralized by the&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/France" title="France" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;French&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="mw-redirect" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aristocracy_(government)" title="Aristocracy (government)" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;aristocracy&lt;/a&gt;&#160;in the years leading up to the revolution, the corresponding brutality demonstrated by the revolutionaries toward the former&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aristocracy_(class)" title="Aristocracy (class)" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;aristocrats&lt;/a&gt;&#160;in the early years of the revolution, and many unflattering social parallels with life in London during the same time period. It follows the lives of several&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Protagonist" title="Protagonist" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;protagonists&lt;/a&gt;&#160;through these events. The most notable are&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charles_Darnay" title="Charles Darnay" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Charles Darnay&lt;/a&gt;&#160;and&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sydney_Carton" title="Sydney Carton" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Sydney Carton&lt;/a&gt;. Darnay is a French once-aristocrat who falls victim to the indiscriminate wrath of the revolution despite his virtuous nature, and Carton is a dissipated British&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barrister" title="Barrister" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;barrister&lt;/a&gt;&#160;who endeavours to redeem his ill-spent life out of his&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unrequited_love" title="Unrequited love" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;unrequited love&lt;/a&gt;&#160;for Darnay's wife,&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lucie_Manette" title="Lucie Manette" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Lucie Manette&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="margin-top: 0.4em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;The 45-chapter novel was published in 32 weekly instalments in Dickens' new literary periodical titled&#160;&lt;i&gt;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/All_the_Year_Round" title="All the Year Round" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;All the Year Round&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/i&gt;. In May 1859 through December 1859, Dickens also republished the chapters as eight monthly sections in green covers. Dickens' previous novels had appeared only as monthly instalments. The first weekly instalment of&#160;&lt;i&gt;A Tale of Two Cities&lt;/i&gt;&#160;ran in the first issue of&#160;&lt;i&gt;All the Year Round&lt;/i&gt;&#160;on 30 April 1859. The last ran thirty-one weeks later, on 25 November.&lt;br clear="none"/&gt;&lt;br clear="none"/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 11px; line-height: 15px; "&gt;Text is available under the&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" rel="license" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Text_of_Creative_Commons_Attribution-ShareAlike_3.0_Unported_License" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike License&lt;/a&gt;; additional terms may apply. See&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" href="http://wikimediafoundation.org/wiki/Terms_of_Use" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Terms of Use&lt;/a&gt;&#160;for details.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br clear="none"/&gt;</review>
